1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
Now that we have our project set up, it's time to start creating our neutral baseline.

2
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Now, to cover kind of the principles of what a neutral baseline is, it's very simply put that we are trying to remove any and all artistic effects in our scene and work from a calibrated baseline.

3
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:27.000
This is very important because without a calibrated baseline, we may be chasing our tail artistically.

4
00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:33.000
We're trying to over adjust or under adjust lightings. So having that calibrated baseline is very critical.

5
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:38.000
Now, some of the things that we're going to do in this scene is disable our auto exposure.

6
00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:42.000
We can do that either on the project settings or in our post processing volume.

7
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Now we'll opt to use the post processing volume as I find that that's much more flexible than setting it just project wide.

8
00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:56.000
We're going to also disable all of our artistic effects, again, also through our post processing volume.

9
00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:05.000
We're going to use some various calibration tools, some that ship with the engine and a few that actually come with our automotive materials pack.

10
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:15.000
And then the important things that we want to adhere to is avoid colorizing our lighting or adding any really crazy effects in our post processing.

11
00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:19.000
Again, we will do this later in later stages of this class.

12
00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:22.000
We'll actually go back in and add some of those artistic effects.

13
00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:26.000
So this entire process is completely non destructive.

14
00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:34.000
And then finally, a another important principle about having a very good neutral baseline is making sure that the materials pack is completely non destructive.

15
00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:42.000
And making sure that the materials that you use to check your scene, to check your lighting are as high quality as possible.

16
00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:45.000
And same thing with your models.

17
